# Application Settings
# ====================
#
# SECRET_KEY:
#   A random secret key used by Flask to secure sessions and prevent CSRF attacks.
#   You should generate a secure random string. For example, you can run this command in your terminal:
#       python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(16))"
#   Replace the placeholder below with your generated secret.
SECRET_KEY=your_random_secret_key_here
#
# TELEGRAM_API_ID:
#   Your Telegram API ID is required for accessing Telegram's API.
#   To obtain your API ID:
#       1. Log in to your Telegram account at: https://my.telegram.org
#       2. Click on "API development tools" and create a new application.
#   Replace the placeholder below with your API ID.
TELEGRAM_API_ID=your_telegram_api_id
#
# TELEGRAM_API_HASH:
#   Your Telegram API Hash pairs with your API ID. It is also obtained from the Telegram API development section.
#   To get your API Hash:
#       1. Log in to https://my.telegram.org
#       2. Navigate to "API development tools" and find your application's details.
#   Replace the placeholder below with your API Hash.
TELEGRAM_API_HASH=your_telegram_api_hash
#
# DEFAULT_DOWNLOAD_PATH:
#   The default path where downloads will be saved.
#   This should point to an existing directory or one that can be created.
#   For example, the default is set to "./downloads".
DEFAULT_DOWNLOAD_PATH=./downloads
